data.name: RL_Introduction.Text
data.value:
Welcome to the ViVeTool GUI Feature Scanner

This Tool is used to download and scan .pdb (Program Debug Database) Files on newer Windows 10/11 Insider Builds to create your own Feature List.

The ViVeTool GUI Feature Scanner is not supposed to be used by the average user. Downloading PDB Files from the Microsoft Symbol Server usually takes an average of 2 Hours depending on your Internet Speed.

This Tool requires:

  • 5~8GB of Disk Space to store the downloaded Debug Symbols into
  • A installed copy of the Debugging Tools for Windows available from the Windows SDK here

After making sure that the requirements are met, set the Text Boxes below to their respective values and press on "Continue". Hover over them to for an example.

After that, the application will automatically start to download PDB Files.

data.name: RL_DownloadIntroduction.Text
data.value:
Now that you are all set up, it is time to download the Program Debug Databases. The Application will automatically download PDB Files for .exe and .dll Files in the following Folders to your specified symbol folder, and will analyse them afterwards:

C:\Windows, C:\Windows\ImmersiveControlPanel, C:\Windows\MediaViewer, C:\Windows\System32, C:\Windows\SystemApps, C:\Windows\SystemResources, C:\Program Files\WindowsApps

This will take a long time.

data.name: RL_InfoScan.Text
data.value:
The Feature Scanner will now automatically begin scanning the PDB Files using mach2

Do not close this Window or mach2, until mach2 is done scanning.

You will be notified by a desktop notification once the scan completes.

data.name: RL_Done.Text
data.value:
The scan has completed. You can now either:

  • Review your Features.txt file
  • Upload your Features.txt file to the mach2 Repository (will appear in the Build Combo Box once uploaded)
  • or Import your Features.txt file into ViVeTool-GUI by selecting the "Use Manual" Drop Down at the bottom of the Build Combo Box
